   129	
   130	## 0.7.1 - 2026-06-01
   131	
   132	EMBEDDER-UNDEFER: the default embedder is no longer deferred. fathomdb now
   133	ships a real in-process default embedder (`BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5`, 384d, via
   134	`candle-transformers`), opt-in per binding, feeding the 0.7.0 sign-bit +
   135	f32-rerank retrieval pipeline with mean-centering. The tag was intentionally
   136	held until the 0.7.2 RELEASE-HARDENING campaign re-derived the real-corpus
   137	recall floor (`AC013B_RECALL_FLOOR`): that work found the apparent 0.828 recall
   138	"gap" was a measurement artifact, the corrected ANN-fidelity number is 0.937,
   139	and the 0.90 floor holds (see the 0.7.2 "Changed" section). `v0.7.1` is cut and
   140	published here alongside `v0.7.0`. See `dev/plans/0.7.1-implementation.md`.
   141	
   142	### Added
   143	
   144	- **Default embedder (opt-in).** `BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5` (384d) runs in
   145	  process via `candle-transformers`; WordPiece tokenization (truncated to 512
   146	  tokens) → mean-pool → L2-norm → mean-centering → sign-bit quantization →
   147	  bit-KNN (K=192) → f32 rerank → top-10. Opt in with Python
   148	  `Engine.open(path, use_default_embedder=True)` or TypeScript
   149	  `engineOpen(path, { useDefaultEmbedder: true })`; default is OFF (no embedder
   150	  configured, vector writes fail with `EmbedderNotConfigured` as before).
   151	  Caller-supplied embedders remain available in Rust; custom Python/TS embedder
   152	  bridges are deferred to 0.8.x.
   153	- **First-use weight download (visible, verified).** With the default embedder
   154	  enabled, first use downloads the pinned weight set from a fixed Hugging Face
   155	  URL set, caches it under the platform cache directory, and verifies every
   156	  file by sha256 (no trust-on-first-use). The activity is surfaced in
   157	  `OpenReport.embedder_events` (per-file url + bytes + sha256 + cache path) and
   158	  `OpenReport.embedder_download_ms`. `HF_TOKEN` is honored for token-gated
   159	  mirrors; public bge-small needs none. This is the scoped opt-in exception to
   160	  NEED-017 / REQ-033 (see `ADR-0.7.1-default-embedder-weight-fetch`).
   161	- **Mean-centering.** A per-workspace corpus-mean f32 vector is stored in
   162	  `_fathomdb_embedder_profiles.mean_vec` and subtracted before sign-bit
   163	  quantization (the f32 rerank stays un-centered). It is pinned once at the
   164	  first 256 ingested vectors and never silently recomputed.
   165	- **Bindings.** Python `use_default_embedder` / TypeScript `useDefaultEmbedder`
   166	  open flags; `OpenReport` gains `embedder_download_ms`, `embedder_events`
   167	  (typed union), `embedder_mean_centering_required`, `embedder_mean_vec_pinned`.
   168	- **Docs.** `docs/embedder.md` user guide (opt-in, first-use download, cache,
   169	  offline notes, caveats, migration).
   170	
   171	### Changed
   172	
   173	- `OpenReport.default_embedder` now reports the real bge-small identity
   174	  (`fathomdb-bge-small-en-v1.5` / HF snapshot `5c38ec7c...` / dim 384) instead
   175	  of the `fathomdb-noop` scaffold identity.
   176	- Schema migration step 10 adds the nullable `mean_vec BLOB` column.
   177	- Wheel / `.node` binary size: the `default-embedder` feature pulls in candle +
   178	  tokenizers and the ~133 MB weight set is fetched at first use (not bundled).
   179	  The feature is opt-in, so builds without it pay no size cost; a per-platform
   180	  wheel-size gate guards regressions.
   181	
   182	### Fixed
   183	
   184	- **Mean-centering is now applied on the production write path.** Prior to this
   185	  release the corpus-mean pin/apply only ran via an internal test seam; the
   186	  async `engine.write` → projection path never pinned, so real ingests were
   187	  sign-quantized un-centered. The pin + re-quantize now run inside the
   188	  projection commit (serialized for cross-worker correctness), with an
   189	  open-time recovery pin for crash-before-pin workspaces.
   190	- **Embedder inputs over 512 tokens are truncated** instead of erroring. Long
   191	  documents previously failed the BGE forward pass
   192	  (`index-select invalid index 512`).
   193	- **Projection workers are fault-isolated.** A panic inside an embedder no
   194	  longer wedges the projection scheduler (`drain` could previously hang into a
   195	  scheduler timeout); the faulted batch is recorded and the worker recovers.
   196	
   197	### Removed
   198	
   199	(none)
   200	
   201	### Known limitations
   202	
   203	- **Real-corpus recall caveat (SUPERSEDED in 0.7.2 — see below).** At 0.7.1
   204	  measurement time, dev-box scouting over the 7,667-doc corpus measured
   205	  recall@10 ~0.828 (95% CI ~0.80–0.86) — below the 0.90 floor — and the floor
   206	  re-derivation + canonical validation were deferred to 0.7.2 (PR-2/PR-3).
   207	  **This 0.828 was later shown to be a measurement artifact** (exclude-after +
   208	  body-string ground truth). The corrected ANN-fidelity number is **0.937 (CI
   209	  0.913–0.957)** and the 0.90 floor HOLDS; see the 0.7.2 "Changed" section and
   210	  `dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-2c-recall-rootcause.md`. Do not cite the 0.828
   211	  number; it is superseded.
   212	- **Topic-drift mean.** Because the mean is pinned on the first 256 ingested
   213	  docs and never recomputed, a workspace whose first 256 docs are
   214	  unrepresentative may under-center. Remedy is reindex (a later campaign).
   215	- **Migration.** Workspaces previously opened with the `fathomdb-noop` profile
   216	  (0.6.x / 0.7.0) fail closed when re-opened with the default embedder (identity
   217	  mismatch, by design per `ADR-0.6.0-vector-identity-embedder-owned` +
   218	  `ADR-0.8.0-embedder-identity-change-workflow`). The remedy is wipe-and-rewrite;
   219	  there is no in-place swap.
   220	
   221	## 0.7.0 - 2026-06-01
   222	
   223	PERF-VECTOR-QUANT (PVQ). A perf-focused release line whose load-bearing change
   224	is **binary vector quantization + f32 rerank** to bring vector retrieval latency
   225	(AC-013) within budget. The workspace was bumped to `0.7.0` (`38d5f4f`) and a
   226	local `v0.7.0` tag was cut, then **held unpushed pending 0.7.1's embedder work**
   227	(per the 2026-05-27 instruction). It is published here together with `v0.7.1` so
   228	the release narrative is coherent: 0.7.0 ships the latency win; 0.7.1 ships the
   229	default embedder that finally lets recall be measured on real text. AC-013b
   230	recall was held OPEN at 0.7.0 ship
   231	(synthetic isotropic fixture cannot reach the floor; real-embedder validation
   232	deferred to 0.7.1). Ledger: `dev/plans/runs/STATUS-perf-vector-quant.md`;
   233	decision: `ADR-0.7.0-vector-binary-quant.md`.
   234	
